    "body": "### Problem\n\nafter moving to native lspconfig from nvim-lspconfig with the update to 0.11, i have found that the `--compile-commands-dir` argument is no longer recognised bythe clangd lsp, or at least it no longer works when in a separate file under an `lsp` folder.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\nin `init.lua`\n```lua\nvim.lsp.enable({'clangd'})\n```\n\nin `lsp\\clangd.lua`\n```lua\nreturn {\n    cmd = { \n        'clangd',  '--compile-commands-dir=D:\\\\path\\\\to\\\\directory'\n    },\n    filetypes = {'c', 'cpp'},\n}\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nhaving this layout in `init.lua` works as expected\n```lua\nvim.lsp.config.clangd = {\n    cmd = { \n        'clangd', \n        '--compile-commands-dir=D:\\\\path\\\\to\\\\directory'\n    },\n    filetypes = { 'c', 'cpp' },\n}\n\nvim.lsp.enable({'clangd'})\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.4\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nclangd 21.1.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nwindows 11\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
